1
00:00:02,815 --> 00:00:05,010
There's enough to blow up
the Empire State Building.

2
00:00:06,219 --> 00:00:08,380
I just met him!

3
00:00:08,588 --> 00:00:09,680
I've never seen him before!

4
00:00:13,526 --> 00:00:14,515
Do you think you can get away?

5
00:00:17,063 --> 00:00:18,052
Would you like a coffee?

6
00:00:19,032 --> 00:00:20,021
A cigarette?

7
00:00:26,506 --> 00:00:27,666
Two spoons of sugar?

8
00:00:28,174 --> 00:00:29,163
Yes.

9
00:00:30,576 --> 00:00:31,634
The temperature ok?

10
00:00:35,882 --> 00:00:37,406
Ok.

11
00:00:37,617 --> 00:00:39,915
This will offend the law. I won't do it.

12
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:42,209
You seem comfortable.

13
00:00:42,288 --> 00:00:43,846
Then should you cooperate with us now?

14
00:00:44,958 --> 00:00:45,947
Cooperation?

15
00:00:46,726 --> 00:00:47,715
You want me die?

16
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:49,318
If you cooperate, you will walk out of here.

17
00:00:49,862 --> 00:00:51,159
We will keep everything secret.

18
00:00:51,364 --> 00:00:53,025
If needed, we will keep you under protection.

19
00:00:54,133 --> 00:00:57,000
If you three could protect me
for my whole life,

20
00:00:57,503 --> 00:00:58,527
then I would consider it.

21
00:01:01,574 --> 00:01:02,973
Don't talk that way.

22
00:01:03,276 --> 00:01:04,607
Even if we release you now,

23
00:01:05,078 --> 00:01:06,067
after you get out of here,

24
00:01:06,512 --> 00:01:09,538
we will find drugs on you.
Well...

25
00:01:09,916 --> 00:01:11,975
we could also find you guilty
for raping young girl.

26
00:01:14,354 --> 00:01:16,049
Have you had good results this way?

27
00:01:16,923 --> 00:01:18,322
Sure. It never fails.

28
00:01:22,595 --> 00:01:24,460
What's the charge?

29
00:01:24,764 --> 00:01:27,460
I've seen a lot worse than this

30
00:01:28,301 --> 00:01:29,563
before going to jail, I'll play along.

31
00:01:44,217 --> 00:01:46,276
You all seem like nice young ladies...

32
00:01:52,091 --> 00:01:53,080
Have you not seen anything like this before?

33
00:01:58,564 --> 00:02:00,225
No! Stop! I've had enough.

34
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:02,731
No, please!

35
00:02:04,771 --> 00:02:06,102
Nice young ladies, huh?

36
00:02:12,812 --> 00:02:13,836
Aren't you going to play along?

37
00:02:14,380 --> 00:02:15,677
I'll sue you!

38
00:02:17,417 --> 00:02:20,215
Say that again. Guns have a habit of
going off when you least expect it.

39
00:02:20,453 --> 00:02:21,647
We'll just say it was an accident.

40
00:02:22,021 --> 00:02:23,716
Yeah. Escaped prisoner!

41
00:02:23,923 --> 00:02:27,222
Good. Get my gun!

42
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,455
No! I'll talk.

43
00:02:29,595 --> 00:02:30,584
Why didn't you say so?

44
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:32,427
Come on, sit down.

45
00:02:32,865 --> 00:02:34,423
Cigarette?

46
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:35,689
No.

47
00:02:37,003 --> 00:02:37,992
There are men in here.

48
00:02:43,142 --> 00:02:44,131
Show's over.

49
00:02:46,779 --> 00:02:48,144
I have sold some explosives lately.

50
00:02:48,648 --> 00:02:50,240
One buyer was a fisherman.

51
00:02:50,950 --> 00:02:51,939
I've known him for long.

52
00:02:52,385 --> 00:02:53,545
After buying, he sold it to someone
who used to blast reef fish.

53
00:02:54,353 --> 00:02:55,547
The other one buys my stuff

54
00:02:56,289 --> 00:02:57,847
to refill empty bullet shell cases

55
00:02:58,057 --> 00:02:59,456
and then he sells them as bullets.

56
00:02:59,892 --> 00:03:00,950
Yet he had only sold a few.

57
00:03:01,727 --> 00:03:02,716
The third guy's name was Polar Bear.

58
00:03:02,962 --> 00:03:05,260
He's a big-time dealer.

59
00:03:06,065 --> 00:03:07,760
He often hangs out at the Yaumatei Pool Hall.

60
00:03:32,758 --> 00:03:33,747
Taxi

61
00:03:39,298 --> 00:03:40,287
Target on a taxi.

62
00:03:40,366 --> 00:03:41,628
It's BP5608.

63
00:03:42,268 --> 00:03:43,257
Big mouth, got it?

64
00:03:43,803 --> 00:03:45,464
Taxi number BP5608.

65
00:03:45,705 --> 00:03:47,036
Heading north to Kok Road.

66
00:03:49,442 --> 00:03:50,431
Big mouth copied.

67
00:03:50,476 --> 00:03:52,467
I see target BP5608.

68
00:03:59,752 --> 00:04:01,242
It changes to TST metro station.

69
00:04:02,255 --> 00:04:04,450
All copy.

70
00:04:04,724 --> 00:04:05,713
Renew info.

71
00:04:05,758 --> 00:04:07,419
Get to TST metro station.

72
00:05:28,975 --> 00:05:30,101
Target on metro heading Kung Tong.

73
00:05:31,077 --> 00:05:32,066
Copied.

74
00:05:34,814 --> 00:05:35,803
Stay there.

75
00:05:35,915 --> 00:05:36,904
Yes.

76
00:06:08,514 --> 00:06:09,947
Target off metro.

77
00:06:52,758 --> 00:06:53,747
Target on a taxi.

78
00:06:53,959 --> 00:06:55,085
It's CW721,

79
00:06:55,328 --> 00:06:56,352
heading Industrial area.

80
00:07:03,436 --> 00:07:04,630
Target off the car.

81
00:07:04,937 --> 00:07:05,926
Heading Yat Sing Street.

82
00:07:06,038 --> 00:07:07,027
Copied. Over.

83
00:07:07,073 --> 00:07:08,062
Sum, your team leave first.

84
00:07:12,044 --> 00:07:13,341
Car to Yat Sing Street.

85
00:07:13,679 --> 00:07:15,306
Start supervision. Wait for orders.

86
00:07:15,648 --> 00:07:16,637
Yes.

87
00:07:27,326 --> 00:07:28,315
I'll take a look.

88
00:07:38,804 --> 00:07:40,101
Pal, where is Pak Lok Street?

89
00:07:40,172 --> 00:07:41,161
Don't know.

90
00:07:41,207 --> 00:07:42,196
Thanks.

91
00:07:44,243 --> 00:07:46,302
Someone carrying two bags heading your way.

92
00:07:53,219 --> 00:07:54,208
Polar Bear.

93
00:07:56,088 --> 00:07:57,077
You went shopping?

94
00:07:58,557 --> 00:07:59,546
Were you followed?

95
00:07:59,592 --> 00:08:00,684
No. Don't worry.

96
00:08:03,429 --> 00:08:04,418
Come on. Open up.

97
00:08:05,297 --> 00:08:06,286
There are three of them.

98
00:08:16,742 --> 00:08:18,175
Detective Chan, it's them.

99
00:08:18,511 --> 00:08:19,500
Must be them.

100
00:08:28,087 --> 00:08:29,076
Three persons' voices.

101
00:08:37,396 --> 00:08:38,795
Louder, let me hear it.

102
00:08:40,266 --> 00:08:42,461
Brother, stop waiting...

103
00:08:43,169 --> 00:08:44,693
All things prepared?

104
00:08:46,839 --> 00:08:48,534
Of course.

105
00:08:49,442 --> 00:08:51,273
Then, I have to make a call.

106
00:09:02,988 --> 00:09:03,977
Not here.

107
00:09:04,223 --> 00:09:05,349
Make sure no one bugging.

108
00:09:06,292 --> 00:09:07,759
Find a place in TST.

109
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,018
Make sure everything is fine.

110
00:09:09,328 --> 00:09:10,886
No wasting time. Get going.

111
00:09:24,810 --> 00:09:25,799
Three persons.

112
00:09:28,414 --> 00:09:29,506
They're coming out.

113
00:09:29,949 --> 00:09:30,938
Copied.

114
00:09:31,183 --> 00:09:32,377
You don't deserve this.

115
00:09:32,585 --> 00:09:33,574
It's you who doesn't deserve it.

116
00:09:51,303 --> 00:09:53,567
Check the number plate
and follow the van.

117
00:09:54,607 --> 00:09:55,869
You stay here, I'll go and take a look.

118
00:10:00,279 --> 00:10:02,372
Right.

119
00:10:02,615 --> 00:10:03,604
Let's go.

120
00:10:08,621 --> 00:10:09,610
We now start the car.

121
00:10:51,397 --> 00:10:52,386
Yes.

122
00:10:52,898 --> 00:10:53,887
Where are you going?

123
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:55,594
To take a look.
Be careful.

124
00:10:55,668 --> 00:10:56,657
I will.

125
00:10:57,303 --> 00:10:58,292
I see.

126
00:10:59,138 --> 00:11:01,333
Detective Chan,
they've shaken off our unit.

127
00:11:01,907 --> 00:11:03,431
They'll come back.

128
00:11:03,842 --> 00:11:04,831
Call them off.

129
00:11:06,745 --> 00:11:07,803
Come back here.

130
00:12:54,486 --> 00:12:55,783
Don't shoot! It's me!

131
00:12:56,155 --> 00:12:57,144
Be quiet.

132
00:13:03,696 --> 00:13:04,685
You scared me.

133
00:13:04,730 --> 00:13:06,595
I fell over.
Someone's up there.

134
00:13:24,249 --> 00:13:25,238
Hold it!

135
00:13:28,921 --> 00:13:29,910
Turn around.

136
00:13:34,793 --> 00:13:36,021
Police! Who are you?

137
00:13:39,431 --> 00:13:41,023
The guy must be deaf and dumb.

138
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:46,971
Did you see three men
come through here a few hours ago?

139
00:13:53,645 --> 00:13:54,669
You ask him.

140
00:13:58,784 --> 00:14:02,481
Do you work here?

141
00:14:05,457 --> 00:14:08,688
Do you sleep here?

142
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,296
Right. I got an answer

143
00:14:16,969 --> 00:14:19,130
but I have no idea what it means.

144
00:14:19,571 --> 00:14:20,560
You ask him.

145
00:14:20,806 --> 00:14:21,795
Take him to the station.

146
00:14:24,476 --> 00:14:27,036
It's OK. You're coming with me,
just for questions.

147
00:14:27,246 --> 00:14:28,577
Come, it won't cost anything.

148
00:14:28,914 --> 00:14:29,903
No need to lock.

149
00:14:33,218 --> 00:14:36,119
You don't need those.

150
00:14:37,189 --> 00:14:38,713
He's deaf.

151
00:14:39,024 --> 00:14:43,188
Are all these toys in here yours?

152
00:15:18,897 --> 00:15:19,886
Stop!

153
00:15:19,932 --> 00:15:20,921
He can't hear you.

154
00:15:32,277 --> 00:15:33,266
Help me find my gun.

155
00:15:48,393 --> 00:15:51,385
Sir! Are you all right?

156
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:54,490
There's a deaf-mute running around,
find him.

157
00:15:54,766 --> 00:15:55,824
Right!

158
00:15:56,969 --> 00:15:58,368
I didn't know he could fight.

159
00:15:58,637 --> 00:16:00,400
Neither did l. Go and find my gun.

160
00:16:00,639 --> 00:16:01,628
Ok.

161
00:16:04,209 --> 00:16:06,404
If we can find the backing to finance

162
00:16:06,678 --> 00:16:07,804
the buyout of Indian Ocean Bank,

163
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:11,916
it'll be a welcome addition
to our portfolio.

164
00:16:12,150 --> 00:16:13,674
Mr Fung, telephone.

165
00:16:14,253 --> 00:16:15,379
I said no calls.

166
00:16:15,921 --> 00:16:18,219
I know, but it's that man again.

167
00:16:19,024 --> 00:16:20,013
Jimmy.

168
00:16:22,427 --> 00:16:23,416
Excuse me.

169
00:16:36,775 --> 00:16:37,867
You called the cops.

170
00:16:38,944 --> 00:16:40,309
No, you must be mistaken.
We haven't...

171
00:16:40,913 --> 00:16:43,746
Cut the crap.
We knew you'd go to the cops.

172
00:17:04,202 --> 00:17:05,226
But we won't change our minds at all.

173
00:17:05,804 --> 00:17:06,793
After 12 p.m. tomorrow,

174
00:17:06,939 --> 00:17:09,271
if you still agree to pay
the $20 million,

175
00:17:09,574 --> 00:17:12,634
publish an ad for your company in one

176
00:17:12,911 --> 00:17:15,072
of the newspapers tomorrow morning.

177
00:17:16,014 --> 00:17:17,003
Again.

178
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:18,405
Where was the call from?

179
00:17:18,483 --> 00:17:20,474
It was a modified mobile

180
00:17:20,686 --> 00:17:21,675
so we couldn't trace it.

181
00:17:21,787 --> 00:17:22,947
We knew you'd go the cops.

182
00:17:23,422 --> 00:17:24,582
But it doesn't change things.

183
00:17:25,057 --> 00:17:26,581
We'll show what we can do

184
00:17:26,825 --> 00:17:28,452
with our explosives at 12 tomorrow.

185
00:17:28,961 --> 00:17:29,950
We won't waste time

186
00:17:29,995 --> 00:17:32,020
bargaining with you again.

187
00:17:32,431 --> 00:17:33,830
Don't worry, they're bluffing.

188
00:17:34,566 --> 00:17:35,555
We've sent extra officers

189
00:17:35,701 --> 00:17:37,100
to protect your buildings.

190
00:17:38,570 --> 00:17:39,559
You'll be fine.

191
00:17:41,373 --> 00:17:42,362
Listen,

192
00:17:42,507 --> 00:17:44,873
this blackmail has gone on
long enough. It's time to act.

193
00:17:50,215 --> 00:17:51,204
Fey,

194
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:52,939
long time no see.

195
00:17:54,453 --> 00:17:55,442
Polar Bear.

196
00:17:55,754 --> 00:17:57,984
This is Ken.

197
00:18:00,726 --> 00:18:01,715
I didn't grass you up!

198
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:02,692
Really?

199
00:18:02,728 --> 00:18:04,753
Why did they turn up after you got caught?

200
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:07,221
Why did they let you go so easily?

201
00:18:07,499 --> 00:18:09,592
Because they couldn't keep me
with no evidence.

202
00:18:10,769 --> 00:18:12,031
I didn't grass you up, I swear!

203
00:18:13,271 --> 00:18:14,533
It makes no difference,

204
00:18:15,273 --> 00:18:16,831
we've made other arrangements.

205
00:18:17,509 --> 00:18:18,498
Where are we going?!

206
00:18:18,543 --> 00:18:19,532
You'll find out.

207
00:18:20,212 --> 00:18:21,201
Miss Wong. What is it?

208
00:18:21,947 --> 00:18:22,936
We've checked the mail.

209
00:18:23,749 --> 00:18:24,738
Thanks.

210
00:18:24,783 --> 00:18:25,772
And these are for you.

211
00:18:26,785 --> 00:18:27,774
Who sent that?

212
00:18:27,819 --> 00:18:29,377
Don't know. Someone special?

213
00:18:29,588 --> 00:18:31,112
If you don't know, who would?

214
00:18:31,690 --> 00:18:32,679
Thanks.

215
00:18:38,397 --> 00:18:39,489
Plant this bomb

216
00:18:39,798 --> 00:18:41,163
and we're even.

217
00:18:43,301 --> 00:18:44,791
Do the job or you're finished.

218
00:18:45,604 --> 00:18:46,593
Where shall I put it?

219
00:18:46,638 --> 00:18:47,627
I'll tell you later.

220
00:18:48,140 --> 00:18:49,129
Let's go.

221
00:18:55,147 --> 00:18:56,239
Roger. Thanks a lot.

222
00:19:00,819 --> 00:19:01,808
Ready.

223
00:19:06,992 --> 00:19:08,391
I'm a cop. What's this?

224
00:19:09,261 --> 00:19:10,250
I'm a cop.

225
00:19:24,676 --> 00:19:26,541
I.D. card

226
00:19:28,046 --> 00:19:29,035
What?

227
00:19:29,081 --> 00:19:30,070
Nothing.

228
00:19:31,216 --> 00:19:32,205
Nothing.

229
00:19:41,359 --> 00:19:43,987
CID. Your case.

230
00:19:44,262 --> 00:19:45,490
Well?

231
00:19:52,871 --> 00:19:53,860
Nothing.

232
00:19:54,106 --> 00:19:55,198
Ok.

233
00:19:55,974 --> 00:19:56,963
What's that?

234
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:03,070
Excuse me, CID. May I see your bag?

235
00:20:12,924 --> 00:20:13,913
The red bag.

236
00:20:13,959 --> 00:20:14,948
Excuse me, CID.

237
00:20:28,974 --> 00:20:29,963
Make it quick.

238
00:20:34,579 --> 00:20:35,568
It should be fine.

239
00:20:35,614 --> 00:20:36,842
Here's the mail, sir.

240
00:20:39,784 --> 00:20:40,773
Roger.

241
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:43,309
Do you think it's a bluff?

242
00:20:43,722 --> 00:20:46,555
I hope so, but we can't be sure.

243
00:20:48,260 --> 00:20:49,420
Talk to you later. Yes?

244
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:56,356
Tell her he's coming.

245
00:20:57,302 --> 00:20:58,291
Roger.

246
00:20:59,271 --> 00:21:01,262
Ka-kui, May's downstairs.

247
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,834
She wants to talk to you urgently.

248
00:21:04,976 --> 00:21:05,965
Thanks.

249
00:21:08,246 --> 00:21:11,079
May. What's the matter?

250
00:21:13,718 --> 00:21:15,845
I've written a letter for you. Bye.

251
00:21:17,589 --> 00:21:20,752
May. You came all this way
to give me this?

252
00:21:21,193 --> 00:21:23,991
It's important so keep it safe. Bye.

253
00:21:26,031 --> 00:21:27,589
Oh, yeah, where's the scooter?

254
00:21:28,133 --> 00:21:31,034
We didn't get along so I sold it.

255
00:21:37,242 --> 00:21:38,231
I'll follow her.

256
00:21:50,288 --> 00:21:51,846
I have my backup units in position.

257
00:21:54,426 --> 00:21:55,859
Yes. I think they're bluffing.

258
00:21:56,094 --> 00:21:57,288
Then we should depend on the police.

259
00:21:57,495 --> 00:21:58,484
All right.

260
00:22:00,265 --> 00:22:01,254
What is going on?

261
00:22:05,103 --> 00:22:06,092
Get an ambulance.

262
00:22:06,171 --> 00:22:07,160
Get the fire extinguisher.

263
00:22:07,606 --> 00:22:09,073
Call Mr. Lam.

264
00:22:24,889 --> 00:22:25,878
Why this happened?

265
00:22:33,632 --> 00:22:34,621
Go investigate.

266
00:22:34,666 --> 00:22:35,690
Stay calm.

267
00:22:35,734 --> 00:22:36,666
Don't panic.

268
00:22:36,701 --> 00:22:37,690
Ka-kui, come with me.

269
00:22:37,736 --> 00:22:38,725
Call the fire department. Come on!

270
00:22:43,875 --> 00:22:45,274
Bring a fire extinguisher.

271
00:22:49,347 --> 00:22:50,336
Come on. Put the fire out first.

272
00:22:51,082 --> 00:22:52,071
Come on, get moving.

273
00:22:52,350 --> 00:22:53,339
Ambulance here?

274
00:22:53,385 --> 00:22:54,249
No.

275
00:22:54,286 --> 00:22:55,275
Go make calls.

276
00:22:59,524 --> 00:23:00,513
We need more help.

277
00:23:00,558 --> 00:23:01,547
Phone, sir.

278
00:23:01,826 --> 00:23:02,986
Bill, you take the phone call.

279
00:23:03,461 --> 00:23:05,395
Ka-kui, meet me upstairs.

280
00:23:13,238 --> 00:23:14,364
I thought you were supposed to protect me.

281
00:23:21,212 --> 00:23:22,201
What's up?

282
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:24,107
Parcel bomb. Miss Wong lost an arm.

283
00:23:39,731 --> 00:23:40,720
How's Miss Wong?

284
00:23:40,765 --> 00:23:42,699
She's doing well.

285
00:23:43,101 --> 00:23:45,092
The doctor said her arm would recover.

286
00:23:46,137 --> 00:23:48,264
They'll do a skin graft
on her face later.

287
00:23:49,607 --> 00:23:50,596
So we'll wait and see.

288
00:23:53,545 --> 00:23:54,807
Wong's decided to pay up.

289
00:23:56,014 --> 00:23:57,276
What am I going to tell Raymond?

290
00:23:59,551 --> 00:24:01,542
Uncle Bill, that's the way it goes.

291
00:24:02,153 --> 00:24:03,450
We said it'd be a tough case.

292
00:24:03,488 --> 00:24:04,420
We're dealing with

293
00:24:04,456 --> 00:24:06,083
an organised bunch of criminals here.

294
00:24:06,958 --> 00:24:08,983
I wish they'd blown me up instead.

295
00:24:09,194 --> 00:24:10,354
I don't like putting lives at risk.

296
00:24:11,196 --> 00:24:12,925
Don't worry.

297
00:24:13,198 --> 00:24:14,722
If they come and collect the money,
I'm sure we'll get them.

298
00:24:15,266 --> 00:24:16,563
If I pass on what you said to Raymond,

299
00:24:17,068 --> 00:24:18,797
he'll not be happy at all.

300
00:24:19,637 --> 00:24:21,264
What we need is real action.

301
00:24:23,041 --> 00:24:24,235
Sir

302
00:24:26,344 --> 00:24:27,333
I guess you've seen the papers.

303
